answers.body_markdown:
Your copy constructor

    Box(Box obj)
    {
        obj.length = length;
        obj.width = width;
        obj.height = height;
    }

does the wrong thing. It will change the `length`, `width` and `height` fields of the given object `obj` (which comes into the constructor) with the values of `this.length`, `this.width` and `this.height`, which are all `0`. You want to write it like this:

    Box(Box obj)
    {
        this.length = obj.length;
        this.width  = obj.width;
        this.height = obj.height;
    }

If you are starting out, get used to using the debugger.  If you put a breakpoint on the first line and then step through the code (often F7/F8) you will find that your constructor assignments are the opposite of what you intended.  The following should work

```
        Box(Box obj)
        {
            this.length = obj.length;
            this.width = obj.width;
            this.height = obj.height;
        }

